<p>Sorry, Coryn, but I cornered the Murphy market tonight.<br />
<br />
Best group I've had in several weeks.  It's raining outside.  No, lightening didn't strike.  It's raining a lot outside.  No, the power didn't go out.  I'm having a great time, experience is going well.  Suddenly my monitor looks like the brightness is turned way up, then the image filters down.  No, my monitor didn't blow up.  I turn the monitor off and realize it's wet.  No I didn't spill anything on it.  I tell my group I'm having problems IRL and am gonna log and poweroff my system.  <br />
<br />
Needless to day I won't be playing EQ for a bit because (yep, you guessed it) <b>the ceiling in my office is now the floor of my office and my desk (and computer) are in that soggy mess somewhere</b>.<br />
<br />
Oh, look...rain is forcast for tomorrow...<br />
<br />
<i>Much as I would like to say I was, I am <b>not</b> making this up</i><br />
