<i>Posted by Borzak on 10-23-2000 08:51 AM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Post" width="15" height="15" border="0"> </b></p>

<p>What can be NERFED will be NERFED.<br />
<br />
Those that can be idiots, WILL be idiots.<br />
<br />
-----------------------------------<br />
<br />
That outta the way, hehe that was pretty funny. The one I notice the most is that 99.9% of the time a buff will wear off during the pull or the first kick (your mileage may vary).<br />
<br />
Snare will stick 99/100 times until the 100th time when you need to make a fast getaway  <img src="http://eqforge.com/forums/frown.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
That one extra MOB you don't need will carelessly wander right in the path of your bow on a pull, ouch.<br />
<br />
Merchants like every letter of the alphabet spoken to them but "A" for some reason, think back to newbie days.<br />
<br />
That one small meaningless item (to all classes but yours) will be looted and destroyed before you can even say "STOP" (like those rings off tidal lords for ivy)<br />
<br />
The one person in your guild that has been in the dungeon you're in and needs to guide, will have a bad connection.<br />
<br />
There will always be 1 person in every pickup group (usually a caster - heheh) that thinks we can go in a little farther or a new dungeon "cause we rock" (ie death by peer pressure)<br />
<br />
The druid/shaman in your group who gripes about having to SoW everyone and that it's a mana drain when things are going good anyway, will be the same druid/shaman who will SoW every Tom, **** , and Harry as they walk by for free.<br />
<br />
Every day you will meet at least 1 person who must have like 12 characters and must be confused about which one they're playing. You know the magician pulls, the cleric tanks, and so forth (oh and YOU die).<br />
<br />
At least once a week there will be 1 idiot selling what you just gotta have and 1 of 3 things will happen.<br />
  1. He/She can't wait for you to go to the bank (Gee I'm in Lower Guk and don't carry around 10kpp)<br />
  2. He/She will decide after you agree on a price after 20 minutes of haggling that NM i'm gonna keep it (or similar I didn't know it was worth that much so I'm just gonna keep it)<br />
  3. You're 9pp short of the 10Kpp price (you actually have it on you this time) and he/she can't come down 9pp.<br />
<br />
Ahhh anyway you get the idea.... We've all been there. WHO knows that could have been you on the other end of the tell from me  <img src="http://eqforge.com/forums/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
