<i>Posted by Lilucia on 09-14-2001 05:30 AM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>You WILL go LD at exactly the wrong time. For example:<br />
You're camping a rare spawn.<br />
He spawns.<br />
You go Linkdead.<br />
You come back and find the camp is taken, the mob killed, and the corpse looted.<br />
<br />
I go LD at the worst times. Usually when I'm just running around somewhere I'm perfectly fine, but then when I'm leading a raid party I'll go LD all night. <br />
<br />
The other night I was trying to make Trueshots for guildmate Rangers. I bought the Kiola nuts in OOT, and perhaps bought too many, because the boat left just before I got out of the shop. I levitated across the ocean and tracked the siren island, as my SoW goes faster than the boat, so I figured I could drop onto the boat as it passed between the islands. It passes by and I land on the deck safely. A couple minutes pass, and I figure I should be zoning within a matter of seconds. Instead I go LD, and when I come back I'm waiting back on the siren islands, waiting for the boat to go all the way to freeport and come back again. Doh...<p><FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2">__________________<br>
